FINAL: Claude Shannon was born on April 30, 1916, and passed away on February 24, 2001. His three key contributions to information theory are: 1) The publication of 'A Mathematical Theory of Communication' in 1948, 2) The formalization of entropy as a measure of information uncertainty, and 3) The definition of channel capacity, often referred to as the Shannon limit.
